3a. INFORMED CONSENT
1 Informed Consent
Participants must be fully informed about the research and must voluntarily agree
to participate BEFORE the study begins. Consent must be given without coercion.
n Explanation: Informed = they know what will happen. Consent = they agree freely. Both
elements are REQUIRED. Consent without information is NOT valid.
n Example: Before a questionnaire study: researcher explains purpose, risks, data use, right to
withdraw. Participant signs a consent form.
n Related Concept: Assent = agreement from children (under 18). Parent/guardian provides
consent on their behalf.
