4a. FABRICATION
Fabrication means making up data, results, or findings that were never actually collected. It is
considered the most severe form of research misconduct because it creates completely false
knowledge that others may rely on.
Aspect Detail
Definition Inventing data, observations, or results that were never actually obtained
Example A researcher claims to have surveyed 500 students but only surveyed 50 —
invents the other 450 responses
Example 2 Reporting a clinical trial result without actually conducting the trial
Severity HIGHEST — can lead to retraction, career destruction, criminal charges
Detection Statistical anomalies; too-perfect data; inability to replicate
Consequence Paper retraction; loss of funding; dismissal; legal action
